OL,3,CTerminally ill Britons could move to
OL,4,CScotland for an assisted death `
OL,5,Cacademic
OL,7,FShe believes differences between the
OL,8,Fproposals being put forward at
OL,9,FWestminster and Holyrood could see
OL,10,Fterminally ill people from England and
OL,11,FWales choosing to travel to Scotland
OL,12,Fto take advantage of medical help to
OL,13,Fdie.
OL,15,FLiberal Democrat MSP Liam McArthur,
OL,16,Fwho has brought forward the Assisted
OL,17,FDying for Terminally Ill Adults
OL,18,F(Scotland) Bill, insisted it was
OL,19,F"highly unlikely" that a patient would
OL,20,Fwant to go through the "upheaval" of
OL,21,Fmoving to Scotland to seek such help.
