OL,3,CTerminally ill Britons could move to
OL,4,CScotland for an assisted death `
OL,5,Cacademic
OL,7,FThe legislation put forward for
OL,8,FEngland and Wales proposes someone
OL,9,Fseeking an assisted death must have
OL,10,F"an inevitably progressive illness or
OL,11,Fdisease that cannot be reversed by
OL,12,Ftreatment", and states that "their
OL,13,Fdeath can reasonably be expected
OL,14,Fwithin six months".
