OL,3,CTerminally ill Britons could move to
OL,4,CScotland for an assisted death `
OL,5,Cacademic
OL,7,FHowever, in Scotland, the legislation
OL,8,Fdoes not include the requirement that
OL,9,Fa person's death must be expected in
OL,10,Fsix months, with the legislation
OL,11,Fbefore Holyrood saying, instead,
OL,12,Fsomeone seeking help to die must have
OL,13,F"an advanced and progressive disease,
OL,14,Fillness or condition from which they
OL,15,Fcannot recover, and which can
OL,16,Freasonably be expected to cause their
OL,17,Fpremature death".
