OL,5,Cacademic
OL,7,FWith Ms Leadbeater's Bill delayed in
OL,8,Fthe House of Lords, where peers have
OL,9,Fput forward more than 1,100 amendments
OL,10,Fto the legislation, the expert said it
OL,11,Fwould "be ironic if the Bill in
OL,12,FEngland and Wales fell because of lack
OL,13,Fof time".
OL,15,FIn these circumstances, she said
OL,16,Fterminally ill patients in England and
OL,17,FWales could still access assisted
OL,18,Fdying ` assuming Mr McArthur's Bill is
OL,19,Fpassed ` if they relocated to Scotland.
