OL,3,CTerminally ill Britons could move to
OL,4,CScotland for an assisted death `
OL,5,Cacademic
OL,7,FMr McArthur said his Bill "contains a
OL,8,Frequirement that anyone wishing to
OL,9,Faccess the choice of an assisted death
OL,10,Fmust have been resident in Scotland
OL,11,Ffor at least 12 months and registered
OL,12,Fwith a Scottish medical practice".
OL,14,FHe stated: "In practice, it seems
OL,15,Fhighly unlikely that someone with a
OL,16,Fterminal illness will want to go
OL,17,Fthrough the upheaval of moving away
OL,18,Ffrom their home, family, friends and
OL,19,Fmedical support at this point in their
OL,20,Flife.
OL,26,@oD@[OUtD@aO]vD@LOU
